<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kivx of E'ci</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-08 05:30:02</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>He CAN NOT see invis at all ... I've floated past him numerous times and walked up to the side of the room summoned a pet and killed him.  He's not soloable by anyone but Necromancers and Mage's ... well maybe others, but those are the only two I've seen successful.<BR>
As stated before, the pathing is bad so kiting is not an option, ESPICALLY fear kiting and I wouldn't reccomend going in there with a level 49 pet (earth for Mage) .. he hits for up to 90-something and procs a 6 second stun, as stated above.<BR>
I've killed him, hmm about 10 or so times now, and I've gotten 2 RS Breastplates and 5 or 6 Claws ... and he didn't drop anything but a few plat the other times.  The harm touch wasn't that bad, from level 45 up you tend to resist it, though this may have changed due to the HT and LOH changes they made.<BR>
If you're level 30 down, I wouldn't reccomend joining this group, usually it's level 35+ with a couple lower levels, the exp is good, loot is good, but there can often be adds very eaisly.<BR>
<BR>
Also in the pool above, there are 3 spawns.  They will NOT aggro in the fight BUT if there are healers up there they will heal the AoF making your fight a bit tougher since they don't run out of mana.  I recommend killing them until you have 3 fighter types up there, not the cleric types.<BR>
I think that should be it.<BR>
<BR>
Kivx Ebonheart of E'ci<BR>
Level 51 Human Necromancer</font></td></tr></table>
